Mathematic Proof
Proofs are not created equal: 
	{ truth, closed-statement, open-statement, conjecture }
✦
Truths are invariant fundamental relationships.
Truths form the primordial structures of a science.

Closed statements are complete groups of relations established into a conclusive formula.
Formulas are directly computational, and are stepwise-reproducible in computation.
Formulas may morph over time, closed-form to closed-form, due to emphasis -- in application of theory or practice.

Open-statements can not be proved conclusive, only assumed by unending non-contradiction.
Open-statement can be stepwise-reproducible, yet non conclusive.
Due the nature of certain open-statements, many can never attain closure.
Development of open-statements into conclusive-closure fully assimilates the statement into mathematics.

Conjecture is a chain of reason; it is a process of the science of Logic.
Conjectures use logical-statements combined with logical-operators to attain coherence.
Conjectured coherence - without explicit stepwise construction - can never enter the science of mathematics.
✦
Formula for the square of a number is a closed-statement.
22 = (2)(2) = 4 
The result is entirely conclusive.

The count-operation is an example of an open-statement: 
	If iteration can equal N, then the iteration may equal (N+1).
Count operation never-fails in Logic, but fails in application space.

When the count-operation is explicit then it is in closed-form.
N = 10; N + 1 = 11  
✦
Induction is the science of foundation construction. 
Induction appends-only proven truths to a system.
There never exists inconsistency in an inductive system. 

’We must start from indemonstratable principles
‘Otherwise, the steps of demonstration would be endless
— Aristotle Posterior Analytics

Truths are only reducible into Axioms.
The set of elements which compose truths of the science is the irreducible set of Axioms.

The set of Axioms form the bedrock of the system and can not be further proven. 
The entire framework of the science is built from the relationships of the Axioms.

Axioms are the foundational elements. 
Truths compose these axioms into foundational reasoning.
Close-statements construct theorems to provide a framework.
Open-statements are necessary due to the incompleteness of the science. 

Each scientist must build a personal set of axioms from ancient truths.
Each Axiom is taken as given by the faith of the scientist.

Sanity forces minimization of the set of Axioms. 
History confirms any new truths appended to the ancient Axioms will be swept away in time.
All built atop these new-age Axioms are likewise flushed.
✦
Deduction is the science of analyzing the universe.
Deductive reasoning begins with an imperfect working set of elements & relations.
	Logical preprocessing, proven by calculation, filters all which is non-coherent.
	Trial & error removes inconsistent elements.
	Over time, the set of inconsistent elements converges to zero.
	The relationship amongst the consistent set of elements establish a result.

The process & results are analyzed into a coherent theory;  all must be direct consequences of the foundation built by Induction. Else the foundation is incomplete or the process was inconsistent.

The product of each investigation is carefully classed as { Truth, Closed, Open, Conjecture }.

‘There are two kinds of generalizations.
'One is cheap and the other is valuable.
'It is easy to generalize by diluting a little idea with a big terminology
'It is much more difficult
'To prepare a refined and condensed extract from several good ingredients
--G.Poyla
Distinguish very carefully between the proof of Generalization and the proof of Abstraction.

Generalizations is a natural evolution, grown from Deductive trial & error in the study of the universe, which distills invariant relations into a closed-statement proof.
Generalized proofs of deduction never assert more than can be constructed.

Abstraction is a term which evolved from the philosophic ideal of universal-containment.
Abstractionism philosophizes a system of thought built in order to attain completion & conformity.
This system is conjectured pure & isolated from the universe; a fantastic fiction. 
Afterwhich, the philosopher forces all analysis of the universe to fit within the ideal system.
The proof is sterile, stripped of all semblance of the universe; as a drawing from imagination.

Abstraction seeks universal-implementation, a pursuit of the lazy & unimaginative. 
Works define the man, and abstractionists avoid calculation at all costs.

‘Definition in itself
'Says nothing as to the existence of the thing defined
‘It only requires to be understood
— Aristotle Posterior Analytics

Proof in mathematics must be constructive by numbers to result in a conclusive number which is stepwise reproducible. All else is preliminary logic conjecture.


Logical-existence-proofs & Logical-contradiction-proofs -- are set at as placeholders for the boundary of mathematic ability.
These logic-proofs assist in affirmation -- of closed statements of conclusive results.
Any theory resting only on logic-proof is immature and underdeveloped, requiring technique to attain the structure of closure.

Mathematics is a forest of trees. Each tree has growth at every level.
Logic-proofs are the buds which may one day grow into mathematic structure.

‘The question of numerical calculation of the limit
‘One of great practical significance,
‘Is usually in theoretical-considerations of very second-rate importance
‘From a theoretical point-of-view
‘All modes of representation for a real number are precisely equivalent
‘Theoretic representation of a number is the Dedekind section
Insufficient in any practical application 
‘The representation of a real number by a sequence 
‘May be considered as the most general mode of representation
Critical in both application & theory 
- Konrad Knopp p. 79

Calculative-exhaustion distinguishes the mathematician from the intellectual-poser.

Mathematic genius seeks the construction of masterpieces as the ultimate expression of superior intellect. Great expanses of detailed calculations orchestrated to construct an elaborate proof converging to a simple comprehension.

Genius is not easily convinced and requires cyclic reaffirmation as understanding grows.

The "necessary & sufficient" attitude of minimum effort, the despicable fault which damns intelligence to the ghetto of philosophy.

‘Every theorem which is complete, with all its parts perfect
‘Purports to gain in itself all of the following:
‘Enunciation, setting-out, definition, construction, proof, conclusion
—Proclus  
Nature of the Sciences of Mathematics

	ARITHMETIC
	Arithmetic is the bedrock foundation of all mathematic science. 

	Axiom of Arithmetic: existence of ordered-numbers in any Arithmetic Space.	

	Nature of Arithmetic is to ESTABLISH an immutable foundation, UPON which many other sciences can find solid construction.

	Aim of Arithmetic is to ESTABLISH the continuity property found in the universe INTO the realm of numbers.

	MEASURE
	Measure is the science dedicated to verify sane behavior of Application-Space under decomposition of the continuum.
	Measure is the analysis of Deduplication of points & Replication-of-loss of points -- in the process of boundless subdivision.

	Axiom of Measure: endpoints of the interval are distinct from internal points, due to the nature of Hoods. Hoods only become consequential when a point inside is set as an endpoint. 
	Exist a Left-Hood from the least-endpoint. Exist a Right-Hood from the greatest endpoint.

	Decomposition of space create two conclusive results: minimum-space required due to Loss & maximum-space possible due to Duplication.
	Nature of Measure is to approach an agreement of minimum & maximum space to a conclusive result, of a direct measure of the space. 

	Aim of Measure is to BRIDGE the processes built in ideal Number Space TO its translations in Application Space in a controlled manner customized to the characteristics of Application Space.
	Measure is an advanced science. Mathematics upon ideal Number Space must be entirely mastered preliminary to adaptations of Application Space.

	Capstone of Measure is to VERIFY, by mesh, the limit of sane behavior of Application Space TO attain the quantity of magnitude, measure, in all possible ventures.

	ALGEBRA
	Algebra is the science of establishing closed and complete relations in the form of pointwise equations.

	Axioms of Algebra: equality of statements is absolute.

	Nature of Algebra uses equality to manipulate statements to establish a perspective-driven chain-of-calculation which culminate into a theorem, this theorem supports a greater framework.

	Aim of Algebra is TO establish static, directly-conclusive, calculable formula FROM complex dynamics observed in the universe. 

	Capstone skillset is to REDUCE recurrence observed -- a pattern built from pervious states INTO a simple formula independent of previous states.

	UNDISTINCT
	Undistinct science cages the unknowable into restricted enclosure.

	Axioms of Undistinct: parameterize space of the unknown --  bounded by knowns.
	Nature of Undistinct science is to distinguish partitions of space as being known-unrelated OR unknown-related. 
	Aim of Undistinct. To approach an agreement of parameters which bound an unknown which will assign a distinct solution to a specific situation.
	Capstone of Undistinct science is to enhance the scientific frameworks of known & distinct solutions, with the bond of the more general Undistinct structures which are framed by known & distinct parameters. 
	
	INFINITORUM
	Inifinitorum is the science of the analysis of infinite processes of the continuum.

	Axiom of Infinitorum is that space is a directional continuum which is populated without gaps by numbers; such that between any two numbers exists an infinite sequence of numbers all greater than the one and less than the other.

	Nature of the Infinitorum uses the directional progression of number space to establish two properties: Divergence & Convergence.
	Divergence grows boundless; after any number may exist another number according to the space of application.
	Convergence endless approach towards a bound which is always greater than a number but less than another number, according to the space of calculation.

	Aim of the Infinitorum is to use the power of approach towards a bound, inequality to contain  answers which escape algebraics.

	Capstone skill set is to enumerate rates of change of the Infinitorum, and to capture the area of space under decomposition of the Infinitorum.

	Science of Congruence, Vector Differentials, Matrix, Geometry, Logic



Arithmetic Space
Axiom of Interval Continuity: between any two points exist an infinite sequence of points defined by the endpoints of an interval.
	Axiom of Global Continuity: A point has no space, thus a point can NOT be isolated from surrounding interval, being Hood of points. The Hood, interval, may be reduced in space but it can only ever remain an infinite sequence of points OR be nullified. No reduction of the Hood can attain single-point-isolation.

	All spaces which fulfill the requirements of Arithmetic is a Number Space. 
Each Number Space has its own peculiarities & noncomeasurables relations to other spaces.

The arithmetic axioms
	Unity: Every system is denominated by a global unit value.
	Arithmetic operations traverse the space. (closure)
	Add-identity (0, -x +x) A + B - B = A
	Mult-identity All numbers are implicitly denominated by the unit value A/B = A/B, A(B/B) = A(1) = A/B.  A(B(B)/B) = A(B)/B
	Distance	
	Add-Inverse
	Mult-Inverse	
