Arithmetic operations:
	(a + b)  Addition— to increment a number by another number.
	(a — b) Subtraction— is to decrement a number by another number. 
	(a * b) Multiplication— to scale a number by another number.
	(a / b)  Division— to denominate a number by the magnitude of another number set as the scale.

Mathematics need consist of these 4 operations.
IF you are not working in the operations of arithmetic THEN you are not doing math.

	Measure does not create a number. Numbers exist independent of the processes of mathematics. A process may generate a sequence of numbers, but it never generates the numbers; such would mean that numbers exist only relational to the process. 
1.414 is an element of many different procedures, and thus exists independent from any process which demands the existence of the element.
Nature of all systems is that the laws are de-localized of the particular-instance; into a general mutual existence. 
To establish a system is to disallow the localized perspective that numbers do not exist until generated locally.
16 is not created by 42. 16 is identified in various ways: by 24, 15+1, 17—1, sequence of even numbers … 

Arithmetic operations arrive at base-10 numbers, but the approach does not create the number.
Number is an element of a continuum; it is a continuous magnitude.

Exist two types of unbounded direction to Space:
	Convergent: the endless approach in direction towards a bound.
	Divergent: direction of unbounded positive/negative growth.

Each arithmetic operation builds a unique space with the peculiarities generated by the foundational nature of the operation. 
Numbers axiomatic existence; property of the numbers are dependent on the space in which the number resides.

Natural Space of Addition
Positive space is the natural space of the Universe.
Only positive measure & magnitude exist in the Universe.
Addition is the operation to measure the accumulation of magnitude.

Space of Addition is a localized space, and not a space of systems.
Local: exist a pile of pebbles which you count. exist a space of trees which you count. 
These actions can never be related unless other spaces exist.
System: exist a store of pebbles. Pebbles are sold to clients & pebbles are bought from sellers.
These actions constitute a system space and can only be related in application space.

Thus the space of Addition is the primary tool to assess a single situation.

Count-operation is the primordial example of divergence; the approach is to only ever expanding in the space of Addition.
Count-operation is an open-statement until a conclusion is reached.
Count-operation tests if space is boundless relative to a situation.
Exist a pile of rocks, each rock is counted, until the last rock is reached.
Exist a mountain of rocks, any rocks are counted, but the process will end and there will remain an uncounted quantity of rocks.

Natural space is whole number space. 
The study of this space is called Number Theory.

