	multiplication is exactly similar to sequences of addition. 
	introduces non-uniform exponential growth
	rate of change become a property

Multiplication is the foundation of the constructive extension of Dimensional Space.
Multiplication changes the structure of space by appending a new axis of direction.
No other arithmetic operation can alter the structure of space.

Elements of Multiplication space contain the characteristics of magnitude & direction.

Multiplication can shift direction of space. 
Positive space requires the operation of multiplication by a negative entity to shift its positive direction to a negative direction.
Negative space requires multiplication by a negative entity to shift its negative direction to a positive direction.

Modern mathematics conflates the notational convenience of similarity of sequence of the addition operation to eclipse all the sophisticated properties which are unique to Dimensional Space.
